                            <comment id="12528867" author="mikem" created="Wed, 19 Sep 2007 20:01:10 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like the following line is failing in your environment::&lt;br/&gt;
assertTrue(str.matches(CONNSTRING_FORMAT));&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Any chance you could add a print of of str and CONNSTRING_FORMAT - it might help a lot to understand what is going on.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12529929" author="myrna" created="Mon, 24 Sep 2007 19:09:38 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This is the contents of CONNSTRING_FORMAT (both on my pc &amp;amp; on the iseries machine, both with ibm&apos;s jdk14) is:&lt;br/&gt;
\S+@&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0-9&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;ins&gt;.* &amp;#40;XID = .&lt;b&gt;&amp;#41;, &amp;#40;SESSIONID = &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0-9&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/ins&gt;&amp;#41;, &amp;#40;DATABASE = &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;A-Za-z&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;+&amp;#41;, &amp;#40;DRDAID = .&lt;/b&gt;&amp;#41; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The (last before Failing) str value on iseries is:&lt;br/&gt;
 org.apache.derby.impl.jdbc.EmbedConnection30@-2073846638 (XID = 223), (SESSIONID = 4), (DATABASE = wombat), (DRDAID = null) &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On my pc, the value at the same point in the test is:&lt;br/&gt;
 org.apache.derby.impl.jdbc.EmbedConnection30@1039214490 (XID = 223), (SESSIONID = 4), (DATABASE = wombat), (DRDAID = null) &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think maybe the negative value after the @ may be the trouble, in which case, this would be a test issue. Assuming that value is allowed to be negative? I&apos;ll pursue this angle.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12530155" author="myrna" created="Tue, 25 Sep 2007 17:55:03 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;closed this issue, because indeed it was the negative value after the @ in the str in the DataSourceTest that didn&apos;t match the CONNSTRING_FORMAT. I adjusted the CONNSTRING_FORMAT in main and 10.3.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
